<P>
   B. anarchy.com The internet is a precious achievement. But as
its reach extends into more of our lives, so does the fear that it
is undermining national standards in everything from crime
prevention to taxation. If politicians around the world cannot
agree on some basic rules, a backlash will force them to act. By
