DISEASE Scientists have identified the structure of a protein that
transports copper through cells. The findings may prove useful in
developing treatments for the muscular atrophy of Lou Gehrig's
disease, an invariably fatal condition. By Paul Candon. Medical
Tribune News Service. 500 words.
