<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE COMMENTARY BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These columns for release Friday, July 30, 1999 are moving today
to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   ERNESTMURRAY-COLUMN _ Remember when life seemed to be simpler?
Before faxes and e-mail and CDs and VCRs, we traveled at a slower
pace. Here's some readers' recollections of the way we were.
(Ernest Murray is managing editor of The Lufkin Daily News) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   BORDERS-COLUMN _ There are four professions whose practitioners
generally take pride in what they do, though the rest of humanity
views them in a somewhat lesser light. Politicians, lawyers, cops
and journalists. I'm glad I'm a journalist. (Gary Borders is editor
and publisher of the Nacogdoches Daily Sentinel.) EMBARGOED for
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   GARCIA-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ This is one employment dispute
with a very long reach. You see, Alex Gonzalez is no ordinary
employee. He's a state district judge with time left on his term.
And the resignation letter he wants back went to Gov. George W.
Bush. The governor's staff takes the position that Gonzalez
resigned and his resignation was accepted and are proceeding with
the search for a successor. (Arnold Garcia is editorial page editor
of the Austin American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   MCNEELY-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ If you went to Central Casting
for someone to play a United States senator, you might well pick
John Cornyn. Gray hair, square jaw, big smile, tie in place over
starched collar, gold state-seal cufflinks _ and better yet, he's a
Texas attorney general. (McNeely, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ People fortunate enough to see
Columbia streak across the Texas sky to its landing the other day
were experiencing something tribal and primal. You could almost see
chariot wheels and winged steeds pulling the traveler. (John Young
is opinion page editor of the Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED
</P>
