<P>
   EDs: This is the CoxNet Travel page for the current week. This
layout will be available Friday by 1 p.m. EDT.
</P>
<P>
   COXNET TRAVEL 0731 _ ISLE OF SKYE _ A visit to the misty Ilse of
Skye in the Scottish herbribes, where the scene of Surf-pounded
skerries (off shore rocks), tiny fishing villages and
mountian-locked lochs has barely changed since Robert Louis
Stevenson's time. (Hulbert, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) Art
includes 4-column color photo of Scottish castle, a 2-column color
photo of mountains by the sea, 2-column color photo of a cluster of
mountains on a peninsula, 2-column color map illustration.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   PRACTICAL TRAVELER _ When allergic children travel, adults who
are aware of the child's situation need to be sure they have packed
a special pillow or protective case, any medicines taken regularly,
inhalers and whatever else the child may need in a medical
emergency. (Wade, N.Y. Times News Service)
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL BRIEFS _ Delta Airlines took the top spot for leaving
ticketed passengers behind in the first three months of 1999. The
line bumped 8,144 of its ticketed passengers, while the nine other
major airlines together bumped a total of 9,167. (N.Y. Times News
Service)
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-FUTURE _ What's ahead for hotels, cruise ships, airplanes
and space flight? Let's trek into the future. (Palm Beach Post)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-SKYE _ ISLE of SKYE, Scotland _ A visit to the misty Ilse
of Skye in the Scottish herbribes, where the scene of Surf-pounded
skerries (off shore rocks), tiny fishing villages and
mountian-locked lochs has barely changed since Robert Louis
Stevenson's time. (Hulbert, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) with
PHOTOS and LAYOUTS
