Trotternish peninsula, the kind of place where Macbeth might have
run into the Weird Sisters. (Hulbert, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). with PHOTOS
</P>
<P>
   Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, August 1.
</P>
<P>
   GETAWAY _ If you enjoy baseball in its purest form _ in a
small-town ballpark under a warm evening sky, at a price that won't
force you to mortgage the house _ then pay a visit to one of these
communities for a game. We detail schedules, tickets and other info
for Georgia's four minor-league teams (Columbus ReadStixx, Macon
Braves, Augusta Greenjackets and Savannah Sand Gnats) and a nearby
Tenn. team, the Chattanooga Lookouts. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). MOVED.
</P>
