<HEADLINE>
CONFUSION OVER THE RAINBOW
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: My best friend and I have looked everywhere _ where can we
buy Rainbow Brite movies or memorabilia?
</P>
<P>
   _J.G., Paradise, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: The best place to look is on the Internet, where more than 60
different Web sites are devoted to Rainbow Brite and collecting the
dolls, books and other items.
</P>
<P>
   The online auction site eBay has more than 200 listings for
Rainbow Brite items each month. Most sell for $5 to $15, but a 1983
Rainbow Brite play set with a dozen dolls sold for $71, and a
shoulder purse sold for $61. Visit the site at www.ebay.com to see
current auctions.
</P>
<P>
   Rainbow Brite was developed by Hallmark and licensed to other
companies. After being discontinued for several years, new Rainbow
Brite dolls were produced from 1997-98 by a New York manufacturer
that has not renewed the license, Hallmark representative Kathi
Nestor said.
</P>
<P>
   The only thing being produced at present are Rainbow Brite
T-shirts, which will be released next year, Nester said.
</P>
<P>
   An extensive Rainbow Brite fan Web site is published at
www.rainbowbrite.net.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am looking for a catalog to order embroidery works. There
used to be one called Herrschners _ is it still in print?
</P>
<P>
   _M.H., Sanger, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: You can request a Herrschners catalog by calling (800)
441-0838 or writing to 2800 Hoover Road, Stevens Point, WI 54492.
</P>
<P>
   Herrschners sells needle craft supplies, yarn, kits and knitting
accessories. The company also sells its products at
www.herrschners.com.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
nn
</P>
