<P>
   HEALTH-CONGRESS (Washington) _ With angry Republican dissension
over health care spilling into the open today, Speaker Hastert said
he only had a long shot of bringing the health care bill to the
House floor next week before the recess. A group of doctors leading
the opposition denounced the House leadership. One House member
accused the leadership of ``going back to the old days of stacking
the deck against anything that doesn't fit the special interests,
the insurers and the HMOS.'' Some Republicans have even crossed
party lines to appeal to Minority Leader Gephardt, to try to get a
bipartisan bill. By Alison Micthell.
