   ISRAEL-DEATHPENALTY _ JERUSALEM _ After two cases in which
fathers killed their children, a few shocked Israelis made a call
for the country to start using the death penalty against murderers.
But, the suggestion was rejected with barely a debate as Israel,
despite a history of terrorist attacks and a rising crime rate,
seems decisively against the form of punishment that is so
prevalent in the United States. Israel has only used the death
penalty once in its 51-year-history. That was to execute senior
Nazi SS leader Adolf Eichmann under a law concerning crimes against
humanity. (Kaplow, Cox News Service).
