<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of July 30, 1999, and thereafter. The stories will carry the ``f''
financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For questions
about stories, please contact Jeremy Bagott at the Daily News,
(818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   WELLPOINT-BID (Los Angeles) _ WellPoint has made a $260 million
bid on the Blue Plan in Colorado. Apparently the bidding was
reopened this month on advice form the Colo. attorney general and
others after WellPoint complained that the Blue Plan was sold to a
competitor for a lower bid than Wellpoint's. By Jason Takenouchi.
(Will move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   IHOP-NYSE (Los Angeles) _ IHOP hopes it can stack up with the
big boys on Wall Street. The Glendale-based franchiser of
International House of Pancakes restaurants announced Thursday it
has filed an application to be listed on the New York Stock
Exchange, forsaking Nasdaq for the Big Board. IHOP officials hope a
NYSE listing will give the company greater exposure to investors _
both domestic and international _ that prefer NYSE listings. By
Dave McNary. (Will move in the ``f'' financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   X X X
</P>
</TEXT>
