<P>
   Business Day Front Page of The N.Y. Times, Friday, July 30 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Coded ``f'' unless otherwise noted): &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Lede story)
</P>
<P>
   FIRST-UNION-RETIRE (Undated) _ Continuing to wrestle with severe
problems unleashed by a botched merger and a troubled business
strategy, First Union Corp. announced Thursday that its president,
John R. Georgius, will retire by the end of the year. By Timothy L.
O'Brien.
