   KOREA-DAEWOO (Seoul, South Korea) _ The government's decision to
take charge of the overhaul of Daewoo, South Korea's second-largest
and most-troubled business agglomeration, has pushed skepticism
about the country's commitment to economic restructuring to the
forefront. By Stephanie Strom.
</P>
