<HEADLINE>
ROYALS RACE TO THE CASH REGISTERS
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; Queen Elizabeth &LR;  is so angry with the  &UR; Duchess of York &LR;  for
peddling her royal image to sell diet products and talking to  &UR; Jay &LR; 
 &UR; Leno &LR;  on TV about her sex life that she is contemplating paying her
off to renounce her duchessness, reports MSNBC.
</P>
<P>
   The amount being bandied about is said to be around $1.6
million, which may be small potatoes (about a hundred calories
each) for Fergie's losing the right to call herself a royal.
</P>
<P>
   As to other evidence of the queen's pique, the duchess was not
invited to the recent wedding of her former brother-in-law; and
 &UR; Beatrice  &LR; and  &UR; Eugenie &LR; , her two daughters, will lose their
``princess'' prefixes when they turn 18.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, &UR; Prince Edward &LR;  and &UR; Sophie &LR;  were in pictures all over
Hello! magazine last week, at the christening of Sophie's
nephew &UR; Edward &LR; . Hello! usually pays for photo spreads, so their
appearance was discussed huffily in such tabloids as the Mirror.
</P>
<P>
   Although Sophie's brother  &UR; David &LR; , father of the child, said
that the royals received no payment, he declined to say whether and
his wife had collected.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, too, 14 dresses once owned by &UR; Princess Diana  &LR; and now
owned by  &UR; Maureen Dunkel &LR; , a Florida businesswoman, will go on
display at Kensington Palace on October 1. Admission fees will be
charged; proceeds will go to the Historic Royal Palaces (got to
maintain the old heaps) charity and the People's Princess
Charitable Foundation.
</P>
<P>
   P.S.  &UR; Queen Noor  &LR; is having Washington lawyer  &UR; Robert Barnett &LR; 
hawk her proposed autobiography to publishers, reports the
Washington Post. Proceeds are to benefit the King Hussein
Foundation.
</P>
<P>
   ``She is a woman of amazing resilience whom I admire greatly,''
said the lawyer-agent. ``I believe there will be an enormous amount
of interest in her personal story.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ J. Shelby Bryan &LR; , whose affair with Vogue editor  &UR; Anna &LR; 
 &UR; Wintour &LR;  is ending both their marriages, has been appointed to the
Foreign Intelligence Advisory Board by  &UR; President Clinton &LR; . Bryan
is a major Democratic fund-raiser.
</P>
<P>
   _ The 40-year-old chairman of the National Economic Council is
``one of the hottest catches on the Washington social scene,'' says
W magazine. During a press briefing on Wednesday, White House
spokesman  &UR; Joe Lockhart &LR;  introduced him by saying, ``Let's bring
out the man Wall Street calls the sexiest deficit hawk in all of
Washington, Bachelor No. 1,  &UR; Gene Sperling &LR; .''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Marc Capobianco  &LR; is dusting off his party hat and getting
ready to celebrate August 9, the silver anniversary of the
resignation of  &UR; Richard Nixon &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; R.I.P. ONSTAGE &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The news is late to reach these shores, but actor  &UR; Bruce &LR; 
 &UR; Mackey &LR; 's tale is pure no-biz-like-show-biz:
</P>
<P>
   Early this month in Chicago, the skull of comedian, actor and
director  &UR; Del Close  &LR; was delivered to the Goodman Theatre. Mackey,
who had died of emphysema in March, had willed it to former
colleagues to be used as a prop, for instance in the graveyard
scene in ``Hamlet.''
</P>
<P>
   Theater director  &UR; Robert Falls &LR;  said it might be used in other
plays, too. ``It will be a theatrical `Where's Del?' On a library
set, he might be there next to his favorite books.'' Falls promised
that Close will be acknowledged in playbills.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THE COLOR ON THE FLOOR &LR;
</P>
<P>
   In need of carpet for a university office,  &UR; Steve Finacom &LR; 
perused the selections of Patcraft, a Georgia company that offered
in its scholastic series the colors Straight A's, Honor Roll,
Diploma, Thesis, Mortar Board and Professor.
</P>
<P>
   The company seems to have a knack for combining concepts and
colors. Patcraft's Critical Path series includes carpets in the
colors Go for It!, Gut Reaction, Course of Action, Sound Judgment
and Reasoning. Its Classified line includes Warren Commission, Iran
Contra, Authorized Personnel and Pentagon Papers. Flashback
includes Psychedelic, Nehru Collars, Lava Lamps, Peace Sign, Flower
Power and Berkeley Daze.
</P>
<P>
   The relationship of the color names to prosaic old red, blue and
yellow remains a mystery.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``Thank God we sent George Mitchell and not Madeleine to
Ireland. We'd be bombing them this morning.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Sen. Ernest Hollings, D-S.C., quoted in the Washington Post,
commenting about George Mitchell's effort to negotiate a peace in
Northern Ireland.
</P>
</TEXT>
