   EGYPT-ISRAEL (Alexandria) _ President Hosni Mubarak of Egypt,
who has considerable influence with Yasir Arafat, offers to step in
as an informal mediator to help settle a dispute that threatens to
sidetrack the Middle East peace effort. By Douglas Jehl. (The story
has moved in ``i'' news file.)
