</P>
<P>
   PASTOR-GAY (Seattle) _ The Rev. Robert Taylor of New York has
been selected to be priest of St. Mark's Episcopal Cathedral, an
activist congregation in Seattle's Capitol Hill neighborhood. He is
the first openly gay man to be chosen to head an Episcopal
cathedral in the country. Church officials say his sexual
orientation wasn't a factor in their decision, that Taylor was
picked for his leadership, preaching and social justice advocacy.
</P>
