   By Tom Paulson. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   AIRTOUCH (Seattle) _ AirTouch Cellular, a provider of digital
phone service, on Thursday began offering direct Internet access
from computers through its cell phones at no extra charge in three
regions of the U.S., including Western Washington.
</P>
<P>
   By Dan Richman. (Story will move in the ``f'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FILM-RUNAWAY (Undated) _ To a degree, ``Runaway Bride,'' Garry
Marshall's re-teaming of his ``Pretty Woman'' stars Richard Gere
and Julia Roberts, squeaks by: their chemistry does finally shine
through. But it takes forever to get going, and the romantic-comedy
results pale in comparison to the 1990 original.
</P>
<P>
   By William Arnold. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FILM-THIRD (Undated) _ If ever a film needed no introduction
it's Carol Reed's 1949 masterpiece, ``The Third Man,'' which has
been restored to all its pristine glory for its 50th anniversary.
</P>
<P>
   By William Arnold. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   TV-INTIMATE (Undated) _ ``Intimate Universe: The Human Body'' is
aptly named. The Peabody Award-winning documentary series about
human life gets so close to its subject that viewers may squirm
right off the sofa, though rarely will they see a TV series so
informative and so thoughtfully produced. The second half of the
eight-hour ``Intimate Universe'' has its North American premiere
Sunday and Monday on The Learning Channel.
</P>
