 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-SWISS-CANYONING-NYT (moved on Wednesday, July 28)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, July
28, about the sport of canyoning misidentified an American
wilderness skills school that does not teach the sport. It is the
National Outdoor Leadership School, not the National Outdoor
Wilderness Leadership School.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CIR-PIRATED-FILMS (moved on Wednesday, July 28)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, July
28, about the illegal copying of movies for on-line distribution
incorrectly described the device used to play movies copied onto
recordable disks knows as VCD's. A VCD can be played on a
computer's CD-ROM drive or DVD-ROM drive; it cannot be played on
any other type of DVD player.  &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
