   ATTENTION EDITORS: The following photos are part of tonight's
New York Times Photo Package, moving Thursday, 07/29/99. Photo
clients will automatically receive these photos via AP's
PhotoExpress or may download them from either the Wieck Photo
Database in Dallas at 972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at
305-448-8411. Non-clients can make individual purchases by calling
(888) 603-1036 or 212-556-4204.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT31) AURORA, Ill. -- July 29, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN., AUG. 1
-- BIZ-PROFILE-FILIPOWSKI, 07-29 -- Andrew J. Filipowski, the
maverick software entrepreneur who sold Platinum Technology Inc. to
Computer Associates for $3.5 billion four months ago. He says that
his next challenge is to turn Chicago into a ``center for
cyberspace.'' (Steve Kagan/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT30) LOS ANGELES -- July 29, 1999 -- ADV. FOR SUN., AUG. 1 --
INVEST-RETIREES-2, 07-29 -- Staying active in retirement, Pearl
Brown of Los Angeles water-skis frequently and practices psychology
part-time. Her husband, Jack Berman, teaches. (Edward Carreon/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT29) NEW YORK -- July 29, 1999 -- CYCLING-ARMSTRONG, 07-29 --
Lance Armstrong at a press conference during his whirlwind visit to
New York on Thursday. Before most New Yorkers could get a glimpse
of the 27-year-old Texan who battled back from debilitating
treatment for cancer to win the Tour de France on Sunday, the visit
was over and Armstrong was headed back to Europe for more bicycle
races. (Andrea Mohin/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT28) ATLANTA -- July 29, 1999 -- GA-SHOOT-4, 07-29 -- Medics
wait at the scene of a multiple homicide on Thursday. A man
identified as a day trader went on a rampage at a brokerage office
Thursday afternoon, killing at least nine people. Police said the
gunman, who remains at large, also shot three relatives at a house
in a suburb south of Atlanta. (Alan S. Weiner /New York Times
Photo) MAGS OUT
